content: Tell me about a belief you revised once you saw the evidence no longer supported it.
What's a recent accomplishment that gave you satisfaction?
What did you value as a kid? How does that connect to what you work toward now?
What's something that turned out better than planned—and what made the difference?
If you're open to sharing, what's a challenge you're actively working to solve?
Is there a system or routine that's genuinely made your life more effective?
What's a new skill or responsibility you're hoping to take on?
Describe your ideal productive, well-executed day.
You're having dinner with anyone from history. Whose leadership or expertise would you most want to learn from?
Who is someone who taught you something that made you better at what you do?
What's something you used to pursue that you've stepped back from?
Right now, what goal or project has your full attention?
Describe a time when you felt most effective and in command.
What's an experience that changed how you approach getting things done?
Looking ahead one year, what capability do you want to strengthen?
Tell me about a time someone's practical help made a real difference.
Is there a decision you're weighing right now?
What's a method you use that others find unconventional but works?
What's a principle that's consistently guided your decisions?
What's one thing you feel is commonly missed about you when people only see your directness?
How has your definition of success changed over time?
Can you think of an experience that forced you to rethink your approach?
What's something you're proud of that others might not see?
When you think about the people you respect, what makes someone worth respecting?
Tell me about a fear you've pushed through to get something done.
When things go sideways, what reliably gets you back on track?
What's a position you hold that most people haven't thought through?
What's been demanding your attention lately?
Think about a mistake. What did it teach you that you couldn't learn any other way?
When you need to truly recharge, how do you reset?
What's something you had to let go of to focus on what matters?
Is there a place that holds real significance for you?
Let's imagine nothing held you back. What would you build or lead?
What's a thought or idea that's been on your mind that you can't shake?
If you could instantly master one skill, what would make you more effective at what you care about?
How do you handle disagreement with someone you respect?
Have you learned anything about yourself recently?
You're gifted a completely free afternoon. What do you actually enjoy when you're not working?
What's an uncomfortable truth you've had to accept?
What reliably gets your energy back?
Is 'home' a place, a person, or a feeling for you? What does stability mean to you?
Can you remember a conversation or exchange that stuck with you?
What's something you keep doing even though it's not your strength?
When was a quick decision that turned out to be the right call?
What's an activity that absorbs your full focus when you're doing it?
What's one area of yourself you're still figuring out?
Besides family, what relationship has shaped how you operate?
What's a question you wish people would ask you more often—one that would get past the surface?
In what area of your life are you trying to be more intentional?
Do you have a personal practice you value, or one you'd actually stick with?
When you're feeling depleted, what restores you?
Tell me about something you accomplished through sustained effort. Was it worth it?
If you could send a one-sentence message to your younger self, what would it say?
What's something that both drives and challenges you?
If you could step back into one moment to experience it again, which would you choose?
How do you learn to trust someone? What tells you they're trustworthy?
What's one thing that keeps getting delayed?
What's a stereotype about your generation that you think is totally wrong—or surprisingly right?
What's something you need but rarely ask for?
What's a piece of recognition that actually meant something to you?
Imagine a version of your life where you fully trusted your judgment. What changes?
What are two things you value that sometimes conflict?
Is there a gap between your confident exterior and your real doubts? (We all have one.)
Do you ever feel like you're playing a role that doesn't show all of who you are?
Is there an 'in-charge' version of yourself that gets tiring to maintain?
Is there something from your past that still bothers you?
What's a past decision you keep replaying?
Tell me about a part of yourself you've tried to manage or suppress.
Is there a moment in your life you wish you could undo?
What's a feeling that runs beneath your composure that you don't show?
Can you remember a time when being responsible for others left you feeling alone?

What's a fundamental need you have that's hard to ask for?

Describe what genuine support would actually look like for you.
